          "type": "tool_use",
          "name": "apply_patch",
          "input": "*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /home/leon0399/Projects/reme/docs/superpowers/specs/2026-03-30-contact-trustlevel-rework.md\n+# Contact TrustLevel Rework\n+\n+**Issue:** #179\n+**Date:** 2026-03-30\n+**Status:** Design approved\n+\n+## Goal\n+\n+Turn contacts into a reusable domain model with persisted trust and verification state, so later relay work can make\n+policy decisions without re-inventing contact semantics in storage, core, discovery, and node code.\n+\n+## Design decisions\n+\n+### 1. Create a dedicated `reme-contact` crate\n+\n+`#179` should not park the shared model inside `reme-storage`, and it should not force `reme-relay` to exist early.\n+The middle-ground is a small `reme-contact` crate that owns contact-domain types only.\n+\n+**Scope of `reme-contact`:**\n+\n+- `TrustLevel`\n+- `Contact`\n+\n+**Out of scope for `reme-contact`:**\n+\n+- SQLite schema or query code\n+- discovery controller logic\n+- relay engine logic\n+- node mode / relay policy config\n+\n+This keeps `#179` as a prerequisite for `#205` instead of quietly becoming `#205`.\n+\n+### 2. Break the client schema cleanly\n+\n+No migration or backfill work is needed for legacy client databases.\n+\n+`Storage::open()` should initialize the new schema for fresh databases and fail fast for legacy contact schemas with an\n+explicit unsupported-schema error. The failure should tell the operator to recreate `messages.db`.\n+\n+This is better than silently half-supporting an old schema and failing later during normal contact operations.\n+\n+### 3. Make `Arc<Storage>` the canonical ownership model\n+\n+`Client` already stores `Arc<Storage>` internally. `#179` should make that explicit at the API boundary:\n+\n+- `Client::new(...)`, `Client::with_config(...)`, and `Client::with_full_config(...)` take `Arc<Storage>`\n+- the app creates one shared storage handle\n+- both `Client` and `DiscoveryController` use the same storage handle\n+\n+That removes the current awkwardness where discovery can read contacts at startup but has no clean path to persist later\n+verification results.\n+\n+### 4. Preserve current `auto_direct_known_contacts` semantics\n+\n+Today, LAN discovery is intentionally limited to known contacts. After `TrustLevel` exists, that behavior should become:\n+\n+- discovery candidates = contacts with `trust_level >= Known`\n+- `Stranger` contacts are persisted for inbox/history purposes only\n+- auto-created strangers must not become eligible for automatic direct delivery\n+\n+Without this filter, `#179` would accidentally widen discovery scope and weaken the current trust boundary.\n+\n+### 5. Trust upgrades are monotonic\n+\n+Successful LAN identity verification should persist:\n+\n+- `verified_at = now`\n+- `trust_level = max(existing_trust_level, Verified)`\n+\n+That means:\n+\n+- `Stranger -> Verified`\n+- `Known -> Verified`\n+- `Verified -> Verified`\n+- `Trusted` stays `Trusted` and only refreshes `verified_at`\n+\n+Verification must never downgrade a manually trusted contact back to `Verified`.\n+\n+### 6. Manual add should promote an existing stranger\n+\n+Once strangers are stored explicitly, \"manual add\" can no longer mean \"insert only\".\n+\n+Required behavior:\n+\n+- no existing row: create `Known`\n+- existing `Stranger`: promote to `Known` and set/update the display name\n+- existing `Known` / `Verified` / `Trusted`: treat as already-added\n+\n+This avoids the broken UX where receiving one message from an unknown sender would make it impossible to add or name that\n+contact later.\n+\n+### 7. Trust UI remains out of scope\n+\n+`#179` persists trust state and makes it available to callers. It does **not** add trust badges, filters, or editing UI\n+to the TUI. That still belongs under `#175`.\n+\n+## Shared types\n+\n+`crates/reme-contact/src/lib.rs`\n+\n+```rust\n+use reme_identity::{PublicID, RoutingKey};\n+use serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};\n+\n+#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, PartialOrd, Ord, Serialize, Deserialize)]\n+#[repr(u8)]\n+pub enum TrustLevel {\n+    Stranger = 0,\n+    Known = 1,\n+    Verified = 2,\n+    Trusted = 3,\n+}\n+\n+#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\n+pub struct Contact {\n+    pub id: i64,\n+    pub public_id: PublicID,\n+    pub routing_key: RoutingKey,\n+    pub name: Option<String>,\n+    pub trust_level: TrustLevel,\n+    pub verified_at: Option<i64>,\n+    pub created_at: i64,\n+}\n+```\n+\n+Notes:\n+\n+- keep `id: i64` for now; a `ContactId` newtype is reasonable later, but it adds churn that `#179` does not need\n+- `routing_key` is persisted even though it is derivable, because later relay/trust resolution needs indexed lookups by\n+  routing key\n+\n+## Storage schema\n+\n+New client schema:\n+\n+```sql\n+CREATE TABLE contacts (\n+    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n+    public_id BLOB NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n+    routing_key BLOB NOT NULL,\n+    name TEXT,\n+    trust_level INTEGER NOT NULL,\n+    verified_at INTEGER,\n+    created_at INTEGER NOT NULL\n+);\n+\n+CREATE INDEX idx_contacts_routing_key ON contacts(routing_key);\n+\n+CREATE TABLE client_schema_version (\n+    version INTEGER PRIMARY KEY\n+);\n+\n+INSERT OR IGNORE INTO client_schema_version (version) VALUES (2);\n+```\n+\n+Expected startup behavior:\n+\n+1. Fresh DB: create schema v2 directly.\n+2. Existing DB with `client_schema_version = 2`: proceed normally.\n+3. Existing DB with legacy `contacts` shape or missing `client_schema_version`: return\n+   `StorageError::UnsupportedSchema(...)`.\n+\n+No `ALTER TABLE`, no backfill, no mixed-mode support.\n+\n+## Storage API changes\n+\n+`reme-storage` owns persistence, but it should stop exposing contacts as tuples.\n+\n+Recommended API surface:\n+\n+```rust\n+pub use reme_contact::{Contact, TrustLevel};\n+\n+pub fn create_contact(\n+    &self,\n+    public_id: &PublicID,\n+    name: Option<&str>,\n+    trust_level: TrustLevel,\n+) -> Result<Contact, StorageError>;\n+\n+pub fn get_contact(&self, public_id: &PublicID) -> Result<Contact, StorageError>;\n+\n+pub fn list_contacts(&self) -> Result<Vec<Contact>, StorageError>;\n+\n+pub fn list_contacts_with_min_trust(\n+    &self,\n+    min_trust: TrustLevel,\n+) -> Result<Vec<Contact>, StorageError>;\n+\n+pub fn promote_manual_contact(\n+    &self,\n+    public_id: &PublicID,\n+    name: Option<&str>,\n+) -> Result<Contact, StorageError>;\n+\n+pub fn mark_contact_verified(\n+    &self,\n+    public_id: &PublicID,\n+    verified_at: i64,\n+) -> Result<Contact, StorageError>;\n+\n+pub fn find_contact_by_routing_key(\n+    &self,\n+    routing_key: &RoutingKey,\n+) -> Result<Contact, StorageError>;\n+```\n+\n+Helper methods like `get_contact_id()` can remain if they are still useful for message storage, but they should no\n+longer be the primary contact API.\n+\n+## Core API changes\n+\n+`reme-core` should stop defining its own contact type in `crates/reme-core/src/lib.rs`.\n+\n+Instead:\n+\n+- depend on `reme-contact`\n+- re-export `Contact` and `TrustLevel`\n+- use storage contact values directly\n+\n+Required behavioral changes:\n+\n+- `Client::add_contact()` becomes \"create or promote manual contact\"\n+- `Client::get_contact()` returns the shared `Contact`\n+- `Client::list_contacts()` returns the shared `Contact`\n+- incoming message processing auto-creates `Stranger` contacts\n+\n+## Discovery integration\n+\n+### Startup load\n+\n+`apps/client/src/discovery/mod.rs` should load contacts with `min_trust = Known` and seed the controller with those\n+contacts only.\n+\n+### Verification persistence\n+\n+On successful challenge-response verification, `DiscoveryController` should persist the result back into shared storage\n+before or alongside ephemeral target registration.\n+\n+Required persisted effect:\n+\n+```text\n+trust_level = max(current, Verified)\n+verified_at = now\n+```\n+\n+### Manual add flow\n+\n+The TUI add-contact flow should stop blindly rejecting any existing contact row.\n+\n+It